					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13860936#post-4829974</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13860936/scp-5594#post-4829974</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 28 Nov 2020 05:57:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Greenburger</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6546643</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>You did a really good job putting personality in all of the characters. I Loved the jokes and the dialogue as well. Easy +1.</p> <p>I only have two critiques, but they're minor (get it). First is a grammatical error. In the first part of addendum 1, you wrote &quot;D-060173 was tethered and given an heat-proof armor, oxygen tank, and night-vision goggles.&quot; It should be &quot;D-060173 was tethered and given <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">an</span> heat-proof armor, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">an</span> oxygen tank, and night-vision goggles.&quot;</p> <p>Secondly is that at the end of the description, you included the sentence &quot;The exact nature of SCP-5594 is unknown and an investigation is ongoing&quot;. I don't think that sentence makes much sense for two reasons. Firstly, that paragraph was pretty specific in describing the effects and entities of the scp, so it felt weird for you to say it wasn't fully understood. In the context of the article as a whole it makes even less sense, since there isn't exactly any mystery as to what's going on by the end.</p> <p>Other than that, it was a very fun read</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
